  "title": "Electron in a uniform magnetic field",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of an electron inside a uniform magnetic field B. The magnetic field is directed into the page. The electron has charge e, and has velocity v that points directly upward.\" src=\"/images/e492a6793bfbc43232e0663c108ed602.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows a uniform magnetic field, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span>, directed into the page. At the instant shown, an electron of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub e\"><math alttext=\"m sub e\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>e</mtext></msub></math></span></span> is moving with velocity <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v\"><math alttext=\"v\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>v</mi></math></span></span> perpendicular to the field, toward the top of the page. As a result of this motion, the electron moves in a circular path. Which of the following gives an expression for the radius of the path and the direction of circular motion?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The radius is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator m sub e, end sub, times v, and denominator e B\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator m sub e, end sub, times v, and denominator e B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>e</mtext></msub><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span> and the direction is clockwise.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The radius is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator m sub e, end sub, times v, and denominator e B\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator m sub e, end sub, times v, and denominator e B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>e</mtext></msub><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span> and the direction is counterclockwise.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
